#: src/0574-drain-range.md:7
msgid ""
"Replace `Vec::drain` by a method that accepts a range parameter. Add "
"`String::drain` with similar functionality."
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:10
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr "動機"

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:12
msgid ""
"Allowing a range parameter is strictly more powerful than the current "
"version. E.g., see the following implementations of some `Vec` methods via "
"the hypothetical `drain_range` method:"
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:43
msgid ""
"With optimization enabled, those methods will produce code that runs as fast "
"as the current versions. (They should not be implemented this way.)"
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:46
msgid ""
"In particular, this method allows the user to remove a slice from a vector "
"in `O(Vec::len)` instead of `O(Slice::len * Vec::len)`."
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:49
msgid "Detailed design"
msgstr "詳細設計"

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:51
msgid "Remove `Vec::drain` and add the following method:"
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:54
msgid ""
"/// Creates a draining iterator that clears the specified range in the Vec "
"and\n"
"/// iterates over the removed items from start to end.\n"
"///\n"
"/// # Panics\n"
"///\n"
"/// Panics if the range is decreasing or if the upper bound is larger than "
"the\n"
"/// length of the vector.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:61 src/0574-drain-range.md:81
msgid "/* ... */"
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:64
msgid ""
"Where `Trait` is some trait that is implemented for at least `Range<usize>`, "
"`RangeTo<usize>`, `RangeFrom<usize>`, `FullRange`, and `usize`."
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:67
msgid ""
"The precise nature of the return value is to be determined during "
"implementation and may or may not depend on `T`."
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:70
msgid "Add `String::drain`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:73
msgid ""
"/// Creates a draining iterator that clears the specified range in the "
"String\n"
"/// and iterates over the characters contained in the range.\n"
"///\n"
"/// # Panics\n"
"///\n"
"/// Panics if the range is decreasing, if the upper bound is larger than "
"the\n"
"/// length of the String, or if the start and the end of the range don't lie "
"on\n"
"/// character boundaries.\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/0574-drain-range.md:84
msgid ""
"Where `Trait` and the return value are as above but need not be the same."
msgstr ""

